node.text:
This definitely got the heart rate up!! It was humbling to see firsthand the true power of a great white shark. 
And while this may look pretty action packed (which it certainly was!) it’s all in the name of science! It is so important to learn more about these apex predators and work out how we can better protect them 🦈
Hope you guys are loving ‘Crikey! It’s Shark Week’ - it’s also streaming on @discoveryplus! 

Repost #SharkWeek

node.title: Bite Force of a Great White Shark!

This was definitely one of the highlights of my shark week adventure! ‘Crikey! It’s Shark week’ is starting now at 8pm EST on Discovery in the USA!

#Repost @sharkweek 
・・・
Robert Irwin uses his dad’s advice to stay safe while night diving with sharks 🌑 

#SharkWeek kicks off with Crikey! It’s Shark Week TONIGHT at 8p on @discovery, but you can stream it early on @discoveryplus. https://links.discoveryplus.com/crikeyitssharkweek

node.text: In celebration of the arrival of beautiful baby Grace, Bindi and Chandler designed a gorgeous range of @australiazoo baby apparel. @chandlerpowell and I set out to see what our animals thought - and help us decide the greatest wildlife onesie of all time 😁 Check out shop.australiazoo.com to get your own baby wildlife warrior gear and click the link in my bio for more videos like this on our YouTube channel!

node.text: On my evening motorbike ride I found this turtle a bit hung up in the fence next to a road and an alligator enclosure (not a safe place to be when you’re a little turtle!) So I took him for a ride on the bike and relocated him to a nearby waterhole. Hopefully Sheldon appreciated the rescue!

node.text: To celebrate 50 years of Australia Zoo, relive our special family moments and the incredible adventures that our dad got up to. We are so excited to share rediscovered episodes of the Crocodile Hunter never seen on DVD in this special 50 edition! Check out the link in my bio 🐊

node.text:
Firstly, I apologise to all Scottish people for my terrible attempt at your beautiful accent! 😂 It’s awesome looking back to these fun times, and I can’t wait to visit the land of the Loch Ness Monster again one day soon! 
For more fun Australia Zoo updates and Irwin Adventures check out ‘Crikey! Club’ online!

node.text: Our lovely Australia Zoo crew made this beautiful video to celebrate my birthday, and it means the world to me ❤️ I am beyond honoured to continue my dad’s legacy and I hope more than anything that he would be proud. I want to thank you for all of your lovely birthday messages and thanks to all who joined us for the celebrations at Australia Zoo today. Looking forward to seeing what this next year brings, in the last year of my childhood!

node.text:
I am truly honoured to be joining The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge to help launch the Earthshot Prize. Spearheaded by Prince William, this incredible global prize will recognise and award those making a difference for the future of the planet. With many challenges facing our world, this remarkable initiative reminds us that there is hope, and that we all have the power to create significant positive change. This will be the decade of action - we can be the ones to create a brighter future; a future for all of us that call our beautiful earth home. 
@earthshotprize #EarthshotPrize

One of our tagged crocodiles heading back to the water. ‘Grace’ is a beautiful old female almost 9 feet long - and with the help of GPS and Acoustic tracking technology she’ll be able to provide us with valuable information about movement, social structure and hopefully nesting behaviour! Interestingly, old females are the most important demographic in the crocodile world. 
🎥 @lukereavley

node.text: While you might think crocodiles are just big tough dinosaurs, they actually have the softest little hands! Today we caught up with an old friend, ‘Natalia’ the croc. She has been part of our research study for 4 years, and with the help of acoustic tracking technology we’ll be able to see her movements and behaviour over the next decade! When we catch and tag crocodiles in the wild, we use all the same techniques that my dad came up with, and our whole team shares a respect and admiration for these amazing animals. We love our crocs! 😊🐊

node.text: Happy #WorldPhotographyDay! Photography has been such an important part of my life for so many years, and I feel so proud that my images can contribute to wildlife conservation. For all my fellow photographers - there’s still time to enter our ‘Crikey! Magazine Photography Awards’. As a judge on this years panel, I am delighted to see so many wonderful shots coming through. This competition has grown and evolved over the years and is now a world-renowned award amongst the photography community. For a chance to make the cover of our international Crikey Magazine, be featured in galleries viewed  by thousands at Australia Zoo and the Queensland Museum, and win huge prizes, head to the link in my bio and enter now!

node.text: I am really excited to have photographed some great nesting behaviour from wild palm cockatoos in the remote woodland on the #SteveIrwinWildlifeReserve. This iconic bird is a very rare and vulnerable species - and sadly new research has indicated that their already dwindling numbers are likely to halve in the next 50 years mostly due to habitat loss. These guys are swiftly heading toward critically low numbers. Being that they only lay one egg at a time in their nest hollows, seeing this female tending to a perfect nesting site is really encouraging. Our reserve is a 335,000 acre area of protected land and acts as one of the last palm cockatoo strongholds on earth.
